'''''Greniodon''''' is a genus of extinct [[gondwanatheria]]n mammal known from the [[Eocene|Early to Middle Eocene]] ([[Lutetian|Lutetian age]], [[Mustersan]] to [[Divisaderan]] in the [[South American land mammal age|SALMA classification]]) of Argentina. A single species, ''Greniodon sylvaticus'', is known, described in 2012 on the basis of two teeth found in the [[Andesitas Huancache Formation]].<ref name=FWGreniodon>[http://fossilworks.org/bridge.pl?a=taxonInfo&taxon_no=327300 ''Greniodon''] at [[Fossilworks]].org</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Goin|first1=Francisco J.|last2=Tejedor|first2=Marcelo F.|last3=Chornogubsky|first3=Laura|last4=López|first4=Guillermo M.|last5=Gelfo|first5=Javier N.|last6=Bond|first6=Mariano|last7=Woodburne|first7=Michael O.|last8=Gurovich|first8=Yamila|last9=Reguero|first9=Marcelo|title=Persistence of a Mesozoic, non-therian mammalian lineage (Gondwanatheria) in the mid-Paleogene of Patagonia|journal=Naturwissenschaften|year=2012|volume=99|issue=6|pages=449–463|doi=10.1007/s00114-012-0919-z|pmid=22584426}}</ref>

